cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this instrument or these results, please cite as below."
title: "Persistence Is Not Accumulation: Erasure, Suppression, and Re-instatement in Online In-Weight Memory for Language Models"
authors:
  - family-names: Lin
    given-names: Xuhao
    email: linxuhao84@gmail.com
type: software
version: v1.0.1
date-released: 2026-07-05
repository-code: "https://github.com/linxuhao/inweight-stream"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - continual learning
  - catastrophic forgetting
  - LoRA
  - parametric memory
  - large language models
  - replay
  - elastic weight consolidation
abstract: >
  Instrument, raw per-fact timelines, and paper for a streaming audit of online
  in-weight memory in LLMs: accumulation is re-instatement not persistence;
  forgetting is erasure or suppression depending on the write protection;
  error-gated replay recalls 85-96% of a 48-fact day from weights at fixed
  budget; online fact writes are readout-proximal (a batch/streaming regime flip).
